{"type":"message","id":"d4fee154","parentId":"a209c863","timestamp":"2026-03-01T18:28:41.907Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Responding to climate command**\n\nIt seems the user wants to start the Tessie climate monitoring process. I'll greet them and ask for specifics about what they want to monitor. I need to suggest starting the workflow for Tessie and inquire about details like the climate subject, required data sources, and frequency. I’ll propose pulling the latest weather data for Nashville and running a quick climate health check while keeping it concise and not revealing internal steps.**Clarifying model information**\n\nI want to mention the default models being used here. So, I’ll start by saying I’m beginning the Tessie climate monitoring process. It’s important to note that I’m currently using google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview, while the system's default model is openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex. Following that, I'll ask the user for the specific location they want to monitor and how frequently they’d like the data. This keeps it concise and informative!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Starting Tessie climate monitoring now. Note: I’m currently using google/gemini-3.1-pro-preview; the system default model is openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex. What location and how often would you like me to monitor the climate data?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":1717,"output":724,"cacheRead":29440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":31881,"cost":{"input":-1717,"output":-724,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-2441}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772389714721}}
